WEBVTT

00:01.740 --> 00:03.351
RENE:
I am Monsieur Trepagny's.

00:03.438 --> 00:04.830
GAY BILL:
If you get out of here alive,

00:04.917 --> 00:07.703
will you tell him
Gay Bill says bonjour?

00:07.790 --> 00:09.748
Previously onBarkskins...

00:09.835 --> 00:12.012
JEROME:
Iroquois have taken
Father Gabriel.

00:12.099 --> 00:15.189
You will entreat them
with Monsieur Trepagny.

00:15.276 --> 00:17.800
TREPAGNY:
Can you help us
retrieve our men?

00:18.975 --> 00:21.064
We will show the way, no more.

00:21.151 --> 00:23.110
And I should do
as I was paid to do--

00:23.197 --> 00:25.503
smash your brains.
Now, go.

00:27.810 --> 00:29.551
HAMISH:
It's Lafarge's boy.

00:29.638 --> 00:32.075
COOKE:
A smart man forgoes

00:32.162 --> 00:35.383
small reward now
for great reward later.

00:35.470 --> 00:36.906
DELPHINE:
When I was a child,

00:36.993 --> 00:38.777
I caught the eye
of a woodcutter.

00:38.864 --> 00:41.911
I kept my virtue.
He made his mark.

00:41.998 --> 00:44.479
-Pierre, I'm sorry.
-HAMISH: I'm looking for

00:44.566 --> 00:47.003
a Mr. Randall Cross.
I'm here to discover his fate.

00:47.090 --> 00:48.570
MATHILDE:
The girl they found
out by the creek.

00:48.657 --> 00:51.355
She's a poor
and damaged thing.

00:51.442 --> 00:53.053
-[screaming]
-COOKE: The massacre--

00:53.140 --> 00:55.925
Cross was sent here
to do that.

00:56.012 --> 00:57.448
Mr. Cross.

00:57.535 --> 00:59.189
♪ ♪

01:01.931 --> 01:04.281
[indistinct chatter]

01:15.205 --> 01:17.164
Come.

01:20.210 --> 01:22.038
Where have you been?

01:30.220 --> 01:32.266
I've been where the blood glows.

01:32.353 --> 01:34.746
We've all seen blood.

01:34.833 --> 01:37.184
No, you haven't.

01:39.099 --> 01:42.363
On a child's face.

01:42.450 --> 01:44.495
The hem of a dress.

01:44.582 --> 01:48.020
The dirt drinks it in

01:48.108 --> 01:50.588
and then it travels

01:50.675 --> 01:52.634
into the trees.

01:52.721 --> 01:54.201
What are you talking about?

01:54.288 --> 01:57.552
The secret order of this place.

01:57.639 --> 01:59.336
It has been told to me.

01:59.423 --> 02:01.991
I came back to tell you.

02:02.078 --> 02:05.125
We've been through some hard
times on your trail, Cross.

02:05.212 --> 02:07.866
You will tell us
why you deserted.

02:07.953 --> 02:11.653
My sister Alice will be glad
to hear that you are alive.

02:11.740 --> 02:13.655
And you will go back to her.

02:13.742 --> 02:16.266
You have a son, Randall.

02:16.353 --> 02:19.400
Tell them that I am dead.

02:21.576 --> 02:23.012
As far as
the Company's concerned,

02:23.099 --> 02:24.579
you still work for them.

02:24.666 --> 02:27.277
You don't know the work
the Company does.

02:27.364 --> 02:29.105
My sister will have
her husband back.

02:29.192 --> 02:31.542
And the Company will have
its account of your travels.

02:31.629 --> 02:33.370
I don't work for the Company.

02:33.457 --> 02:35.938
I have given it all up.

02:36.025 --> 02:38.027
Now, let me go

02:38.114 --> 02:40.421
and be lost again.

02:44.164 --> 02:45.600
HAMISH:
We will get our answers.

02:45.687 --> 02:47.254
Randall.

02:47.341 --> 02:49.386
You will come with us at once.

02:54.043 --> 02:56.088
Would you like to hear a story?

02:56.176 --> 02:57.133
No.

02:57.220 --> 02:58.526
I would not.

03:00.789 --> 03:02.791
♪ ♪

03:13.410 --> 03:15.369
[chatter in distance]

03:40.785 --> 03:42.874
TREPAGNY [whispering]:
Take in the details.

03:42.961 --> 03:45.094
Set a careful plan, Captain.

03:45.181 --> 03:46.835
The plan is I will kill

03:46.922 --> 03:49.359
three savages,
Deputy Guy is good for two,

03:49.446 --> 03:50.752
though he is a poor shot.

03:50.839 --> 03:53.015
That leaves one for you,
Trepagny.

03:53.102 --> 03:56.018
De Fer ordered us to entreat,
not attack.

03:56.105 --> 03:58.325
Plans rarely go
as one might expect.

03:58.412 --> 04:01.415
-Oh, killed many savages,
have you?
-I have not had the misfortune,

04:01.502 --> 04:03.808
but I was at the
Battle of the Dunes
with Cardinal Mazarin.

04:03.895 --> 04:06.376
I don't give a cold piss
about the Dunes.

04:06.463 --> 04:10.119
We have pistols and muskets.
They have pointy sticks.

04:10.206 --> 04:12.991
All plans were smashed that day.

04:13.078 --> 04:16.168
Now is not the time to fill
your boot leather with mud.

04:16.256 --> 04:19.171
I don't intend to die
rescuing a priest.

04:19.259 --> 04:22.044
-Sel is down there.
-That goes double
for your indentured man.

04:22.131 --> 04:23.741
I'd rather die for my hat.

04:28.877 --> 04:30.357
GUY:
Any sign of them?

04:30.444 --> 04:32.010
Six savages.

04:32.097 --> 04:33.447
Father Gabriel?

04:35.579 --> 04:37.320
He may already be dead.

04:39.279 --> 04:41.890
[Bouchard laughs]

04:41.977 --> 04:43.805
You're in the belly
of the whale now, Father.

04:43.892 --> 04:45.285
Come, share a drink with me.

04:46.982 --> 04:49.289
Father Gabriel is not dead.

04:49.376 --> 04:51.552
Sel is there.

04:51.639 --> 04:53.336
Alive, I believe.

04:53.423 --> 04:55.120
We shall put them
under the musket.

04:55.207 --> 04:56.644
And they shall fold
under our might.

04:56.731 --> 04:58.602
No, Captain.

04:58.689 --> 05:00.517
Father Clape and I
will entreat them.

05:00.604 --> 05:04.173
The Iroquois
are not like other tribes.

05:04.260 --> 05:07.655
They will not be receptive
to your enticements
of an afterlife.

05:09.439 --> 05:11.789
All creatures hear
the word of the Lord equally,

05:11.876 --> 05:13.269
Monsieur Trepagny.

05:13.356 --> 05:15.271
Now is not the time
to debate, Father,

05:15.358 --> 05:18.056
but once I read
the Book of Ezekiel,

05:18.143 --> 05:20.711
chapter one,
verses one through 16

05:20.798 --> 05:22.191
to a field toad.

05:22.278 --> 05:24.715
Do you know what it did?

05:24.802 --> 05:26.587
It hopped away.

05:26.674 --> 05:28.284
It wanted a worm.

05:28.371 --> 05:30.678
Not the word of God.

05:30.765 --> 05:34.421
The Lord shall wrap us in his
shroud of heavenly protection.

05:34.508 --> 05:38.207
Where was that shroud when
they took Father Gabriel?

05:38.294 --> 05:39.643
Father Gabriel is being tested.

05:39.730 --> 05:41.906
Father Gabriel
is being tortured.

05:41.993 --> 05:44.256
We will entreat the Iroquois

05:44.344 --> 05:46.824
and discuss
a peaceful resolution.

05:46.911 --> 05:49.174
You entreat all you want,
Father,

05:49.261 --> 05:52.003
after we've put some
savage souls in dog hell.

05:54.441 --> 05:56.181
Ah, yes, consult
the good book, Father.

05:56.268 --> 05:58.314
There's a fair bit
of wisdom in there about

05:58.401 --> 05:59.881
the time to sort
the world with smiting.

05:59.968 --> 06:03.188
There will be no smiting.

06:03.275 --> 06:05.887
Now, come on, Father.

06:08.498 --> 06:10.152
Come on.

06:10.239 --> 06:12.241
Bonne chance.

06:13.677 --> 06:15.287
The heavenly ladder is slick

06:15.375 --> 06:17.551
with the blood of martyrs.

07:02.291 --> 07:03.858
JEROME:
I come in peace.

07:03.945 --> 07:06.426
I am sent with treaties
from Intendant De Fer

07:06.513 --> 07:07.949
that want me
to end the bloodshed.

07:10.299 --> 07:12.040
Save the last swallow
for when the killing's done.

07:12.127 --> 07:13.389
JEROME:
We mean no harm.

07:13.476 --> 07:15.826
As you can see,
we are not armed.

07:15.913 --> 07:18.786
It seems Father Jerome's
sour face

07:18.873 --> 07:20.309
is quite charming after all.

07:20.396 --> 07:22.616
JEROME:
For our brother, Father Gabriel.

07:22.703 --> 07:24.748
BOUCHARD:
Can this be the mystical shroud

07:24.835 --> 07:26.794
the Father was talking about?

07:32.234 --> 07:34.366
Take dead aim

07:34.454 --> 07:37.239
and pray your ball
finds savage skull.

07:37.326 --> 07:39.197
GABRIEL:
Help me, Father.

07:39.284 --> 07:42.200
Help me.

07:42.287 --> 07:45.377
If your people go out to battle
against His enemies,

07:45.465 --> 07:48.206
then you shall hear in heaven

07:48.293 --> 07:50.600
and you shall vindicate them.

07:55.475 --> 07:57.433
Aw, hell.

07:58.390 --> 08:00.131
[whooping]

08:02.133 --> 08:03.308
Follow!

08:03.395 --> 08:05.485
[men shouting, screaming]

08:10.881 --> 08:12.056
[groans]

08:15.712 --> 08:17.235
[grunting]

08:42.870 --> 08:45.350
[both grunting]

09:11.028 --> 09:12.639
Aah!

09:20.081 --> 09:22.387
RENE:
Bouchard.

09:26.870 --> 09:29.656
Don't let that dog get away.

09:43.670 --> 09:45.628
♪ ♪

10:06.344 --> 10:08.303
[indistinct chatter]

10:11.654 --> 10:13.613
Delphine.

10:15.615 --> 10:17.617
For the intendant.

10:21.533 --> 10:24.406
Oh, that looks good.

10:24.493 --> 10:27.104
And... I must say

10:27.191 --> 10:28.715
that I am being served

10:28.802 --> 10:31.195
by a very charming lady.

10:31.282 --> 10:32.980
Don't be shy.

10:33.067 --> 10:35.373
[laughs]

10:35.460 --> 10:38.028
You caught
the Intendant De Fer's eye.

10:38.115 --> 10:39.247
I did?

10:39.334 --> 10:40.640
Oh, come now, Delphine.

10:40.727 --> 10:43.381
I saw him lean in
to see your face.

10:43.468 --> 10:44.687
What did he say?

10:44.774 --> 10:46.820
He thanked me for the ham.

10:46.907 --> 10:48.952
Surely there was
more than that.

10:49.039 --> 10:51.781
I don't know,
per-perhaps a compliment.

10:51.868 --> 10:55.045
[groans]
Put your shoulders back, smile.

10:55.132 --> 10:56.612
The food tastes better
when the one serving it

10:56.699 --> 10:58.005
has some polish.

10:58.092 --> 10:59.659
I am still trying
to find my place.

10:59.746 --> 11:01.269
Your place is here now,
and I can't

11:01.356 --> 11:03.706
have you walking around
like some cut flower.

11:03.793 --> 11:06.100
-I will try.
-Of course you will.

11:06.187 --> 11:08.102
You have nowhere else to go.

11:08.189 --> 11:11.148
Come now, I am just speaking
a simple truth.

11:11.235 --> 11:13.411
The inn is not so bad.

11:13.498 --> 11:16.980
Better than a dark cabin
in the woods.

11:17.067 --> 11:20.549
Now then, I aim to expand.

11:20.636 --> 11:23.770
More room for dining,
away from the billiards.

11:23.857 --> 11:26.903
A place for the men to sit
and put their hand to drink

11:26.990 --> 11:29.384
and tell their stories.
[laughs]

11:29.471 --> 11:31.952
And a place for the women,

11:32.039 --> 11:34.215
away from the men,
should they wish.

11:34.302 --> 11:36.043
Do you have any ideas?

11:36.130 --> 11:37.958
Rabbits.

11:39.046 --> 11:42.353
Yes, Renardette, more rabbits.

11:42.440 --> 11:44.312
What about you, Delphine?

11:44.399 --> 11:45.748
I don't know.

11:45.835 --> 11:48.229
You don't know or you won't say?

11:48.316 --> 11:50.927
I want to hear your opinions.

11:51.014 --> 11:52.668
Mmm.

11:52.755 --> 11:54.714
Come.

11:54.801 --> 11:58.152
Help me fetch some prune tart.
We need three pieces.

11:58.239 --> 11:59.806
Renardette, brandy.

11:59.893 --> 12:03.418
I have some unpleasant business
to attend to.

12:03.505 --> 12:05.594
It will be good
to have you by my side.

12:05.681 --> 12:08.031
Uh...

12:08.118 --> 12:10.338
[chuckles softly]

12:10.425 --> 12:12.035
Come.

12:13.515 --> 12:16.126
[chuckles]

12:16.213 --> 12:19.086
Uh, no, no. It is better
for you to stay here, dear.

12:19.173 --> 12:21.175
The man, Mr. Cross, is up there.

12:21.262 --> 12:22.785
I want to see.

12:22.872 --> 12:24.831
No.
You stay down here.

12:24.918 --> 12:26.833
Cut onions.

12:35.755 --> 12:37.713
HAMISH:
Come, Randall.

12:37.800 --> 12:40.585
Look upon Alice.
Her kind and beautiful face.

12:42.326 --> 12:43.719
[scoffs]

12:43.806 --> 12:46.722
She's not kind.
[chuckles]

12:46.809 --> 12:48.985
The image does not
do her justice.

12:49.072 --> 12:50.987
CROSS:
Her eyes--

12:51.074 --> 12:53.076
cold, black stones.

12:53.163 --> 12:54.686
I remember them well.

12:54.774 --> 12:58.386
They are not black.
They are brown.

12:59.735 --> 13:02.172
And I will not
let you abandon her.

13:02.259 --> 13:04.740
Then you may go back to her.

13:04.827 --> 13:07.264
Attend to sweet Alice

13:07.351 --> 13:09.919
and her worries.

13:10.006 --> 13:12.704
Captain Wale says you were
supposed to deliver something.

13:12.792 --> 13:13.967
What?

13:15.620 --> 13:17.622
[knocking]

13:24.020 --> 13:25.979
Come in, Mathilde.

13:30.592 --> 13:33.160
I am afraid I am going
to be needing the room back.

13:33.247 --> 13:34.465
Randall has not yet
sufficiently recovered.

13:34.552 --> 13:36.424
YVON:
How is the room needed

13:36.511 --> 13:38.295
if we are in it?

13:38.382 --> 13:40.907
The Intendant De Fer
has taken notice

13:40.994 --> 13:42.865
of the English presence.

13:42.952 --> 13:45.041
So it is his wish that we should
be put out of a room

13:45.128 --> 13:46.913
-we've already paid for?
-I have made some brandy here

13:47.000 --> 13:48.784
and prune tart for you.

13:48.871 --> 13:51.569
Uh, it does not begin to make up
for the sudden notice.

13:51.656 --> 13:53.571
Nor does it repay
the debt I owe you

13:53.658 --> 13:56.052
for defending my inn
against Gus Lafarge.

13:56.139 --> 13:58.576
But please, you...
Renardette?

13:58.663 --> 14:01.579
What are you doing?

14:01.666 --> 14:02.885
Get back here.

14:10.023 --> 14:12.155
That is enough, Renardette.
Come.

14:12.242 --> 14:15.332
Take her downstairs.
Excuse me.

14:15.419 --> 14:17.595
Go, Renardette.
Please.

14:19.293 --> 14:21.382
As you can see,

14:21.469 --> 14:24.385
his presence
has upset poor Renardette.

14:24.472 --> 14:26.430
You have recovered, Mr. Cross.

14:26.517 --> 14:30.347
Now, I am sure he is eager
to go home, leave Wobik.

14:31.871 --> 14:33.611
So, if you will please accept

14:33.698 --> 14:36.788
this small gift and begone.

14:38.486 --> 14:39.879
[sighs]
We will gather our things

14:39.966 --> 14:41.619
and part on good terms.

14:41.706 --> 14:44.318
I would not want to put you
in a strange position

14:44.405 --> 14:45.623
with Intendant De Fer.

14:45.710 --> 14:47.712
Merci.

14:54.241 --> 14:56.199
[birds chirping]

15:20.615 --> 15:22.530
[sighs]

15:22.617 --> 15:24.619
[groans softly]

15:40.417 --> 15:42.376
♪ ♪

16:01.961 --> 16:03.963
♪ ♪

16:14.886 --> 16:16.105
[clattering in distance]

16:25.071 --> 16:27.029
[clattering continues]

16:33.514 --> 16:35.820
What is this?

16:35.907 --> 16:37.822
My mother gave these to me.

16:37.909 --> 16:40.434
I cooked my first meal
for Mr. Trepagny with them.

16:40.521 --> 16:41.826
They're yours, then.

16:41.913 --> 16:43.611
And the house is yours.

16:43.698 --> 16:46.005
All of it.

16:47.484 --> 16:49.834
I am leaving.
You may tell him that.

16:49.921 --> 16:51.488
He has not returned yet.

16:56.493 --> 16:58.887
The Iroquois will
put his body in a tree.

16:59.975 --> 17:02.934
The Doma will be put to a torch.

17:03.022 --> 17:06.721
And then
they will come for you.

17:08.201 --> 17:11.813
Take your pot and leave.

17:20.082 --> 17:22.867
If he does return,

17:22.954 --> 17:25.131
tell him I saw what
the ram's insides spoke of.

17:25.218 --> 17:27.263
What are you talking about?

17:28.351 --> 17:30.353
Tell him I saw his end.

17:30.440 --> 17:33.052
Get out!
Now!

17:51.070 --> 17:53.072
♪ ♪

18:18.358 --> 18:20.316
♪ ♪

18:41.946 --> 18:43.383
BOUCHARD:
Trepagny.

18:43.470 --> 18:45.298
Bouchard.

18:46.908 --> 18:49.345
I'm leaking, but alive.

18:49.432 --> 18:50.912
You?

18:54.481 --> 18:56.657
Painfully alive.

19:09.626 --> 19:11.672
BOUCHARD:
A bad day for the black robes.

19:13.239 --> 19:16.285
Thin one fell on the fat one
and killed him.

19:17.852 --> 19:21.682
We will have to answer for this.

19:21.769 --> 19:24.293
[sighs]
Yes.

19:24.380 --> 19:26.730
Yes, we will.

19:26.817 --> 19:29.777
Now it is our duty
to put them into the dirt.

19:31.866 --> 19:33.998
I will attend to Hawahstha'.

19:34.085 --> 19:36.087
Leave him in the sun,
he will turn to mud.

19:36.175 --> 19:39.917
No, we will return him
to the Wyandot.

19:40.004 --> 19:41.571
Without them, your entrails

19:41.658 --> 19:44.095
would decorate these rocks.

19:44.183 --> 19:46.924
-Where is Sel?
-Oh, he went that way.

19:47.011 --> 19:50.145
After the last savage.

19:50.232 --> 19:52.974
Both of them dead in the trees,
most likely.

19:53.061 --> 19:56.238
No, no, no, no.
He is alive, I feel it.

19:59.154 --> 20:01.112
Well...

20:01.200 --> 20:03.593
[clears throat]

20:03.680 --> 20:06.074
Let's go find your man.

20:10.252 --> 20:12.994
[grunts]

20:22.830 --> 20:24.832
[grunts]

20:41.979 --> 20:43.372
GAY BILL:
You're not gonna be able to stab

20:43.459 --> 20:45.722
your way out of this one,
French.

20:45.809 --> 20:48.725
I mean, you're welcome to try.

20:48.812 --> 20:51.162
But...

20:51.250 --> 20:53.556
they'll take
that little knife of yours

20:53.643 --> 20:56.951
and they'll make a wee cut,
right here.

20:57.038 --> 20:58.996
They'll reach in,

20:59.083 --> 21:01.434
real gentle-like,

21:01.521 --> 21:03.479
pull out your guts,

21:03.566 --> 21:05.699
feed them to the dogs
while you watch.

21:05.786 --> 21:07.831
Now, the dogs--

21:07.918 --> 21:10.399
they don't go far at first,
but soon,

21:10.486 --> 21:12.227
they get to frisking,
competing with each other,

21:12.314 --> 21:15.578
and before you know it,
they've got you unspooled.

21:18.102 --> 21:20.670
I am prepared to die.

21:22.106 --> 21:24.674
GAY BILL:
Such brave and grand words.

21:25.762 --> 21:26.894
Let him go.

21:28.591 --> 21:30.506
My men are dead.

21:30.593 --> 21:34.467
My brother is dead.

21:34.554 --> 21:36.338
He should be fed to the dogs.

21:36.425 --> 21:39.298
The French in Wobik are
responsible, but not this one.

21:39.385 --> 21:41.125
I mean, look at him.

21:41.212 --> 21:43.737
He's a simple man.

21:43.824 --> 21:46.305
Your father would spare him.

21:48.394 --> 21:52.267
Because... more will come.

21:54.051 --> 21:55.966
Isn't that right, French?

21:56.053 --> 21:59.535
And then we can kill them all.
It's what we both want.

21:59.622 --> 22:02.146
Hmm.

22:02.233 --> 22:04.235
Now...

22:04.323 --> 22:08.109
I should like to sit by a fire,

22:08.196 --> 22:10.198
take off my boots,

22:10.285 --> 22:12.243
have a meal,

22:12.331 --> 22:14.811
a proper shit.

22:15.899 --> 22:17.858
The stuff of life.

22:19.338 --> 22:22.079
Go on, French.
Walk.

22:24.386 --> 22:27.520
Tell them Gay Bill
is a kind and wise man.

22:29.870 --> 22:31.654
Off you trot.

22:45.581 --> 22:47.583
You let a savage into the house.

22:47.670 --> 22:48.802
I-I did?

22:48.889 --> 22:50.499
Yes, inside.

22:50.586 --> 22:53.937
The housekeeper?
Y-Yes.

22:56.200 --> 22:58.768
Do you like roses?

22:58.855 --> 23:00.466
They look magnificent,
don't you think?

23:00.553 --> 23:03.077
They look like roses.

23:03.164 --> 23:05.384
Now I wish to be escorted
back to Wobik.

23:05.471 --> 23:07.386
-It is not safe here.
-Hey, no, no. I...

23:07.473 --> 23:09.039
I will keep you safe.

23:09.126 --> 23:11.085
Hmm.
Picking flowers?

23:13.304 --> 23:15.698
I have orders to wait here.

23:15.785 --> 23:18.005
-Orders from whom?
-Captain Bouchard.

23:19.093 --> 23:22.052
He... he beats me on my head

23:22.139 --> 23:23.706
when I don't do
as he says, so...

23:23.793 --> 23:26.056
Hmm.

23:26.143 --> 23:28.885
Tell me, what do you think
Monsieur Trepagny will do

23:28.972 --> 23:31.453
if he discovers that
you have let his new bride

23:31.540 --> 23:33.977
take the path to Wobik alone,

23:34.064 --> 23:36.110
unguarded?

23:36.197 --> 23:39.461
It will be worse
than Captain Bouchard's blows.

23:39.548 --> 23:41.942
We-we must not leave here.

23:42.029 --> 23:43.422
They will be back soon.

23:43.509 --> 23:45.946
I will be waiting
on the path, Deputy.

24:03.529 --> 24:05.444
-[rustling]
-Shh, shh, shh.

24:16.629 --> 24:19.675
-Monsieur Sel!
-Shh. Iroquois.

24:19.762 --> 24:23.374
There are too many.
An Englishman, too.

24:23.462 --> 24:26.073
English?

24:26.160 --> 24:27.596
How far?

24:27.683 --> 24:29.032
Just through the woods.

24:29.119 --> 24:30.686
TREPAGNY:
How did you escape?

24:30.773 --> 24:32.732
The Englishman convinced them.

24:34.385 --> 24:35.561
Bouchard.

24:37.954 --> 24:41.088
We have dodged death's
warm embrace once today.

24:41.175 --> 24:43.917
I do not wish to tempt
its coils again.

24:44.004 --> 24:46.267
We must return to Wobik
and warn them.

24:52.142 --> 24:53.535
Your man is right.

24:53.622 --> 24:56.103
The Iroquois will come
and kill us all.

25:04.415 --> 25:05.721
[indistinct chatter]

25:10.987 --> 25:12.249
Yvon.

25:14.338 --> 25:17.211
I'll meet you on the path.

25:17.298 --> 25:19.474
Keep a close eye on him.

25:24.914 --> 25:26.437
COOKE:
You recovered Mr. Cross?

25:26.525 --> 25:27.917
I have.

25:29.919 --> 25:31.791
Well?

25:31.878 --> 25:34.533
What did he have
to say for himself?

25:34.620 --> 25:35.882
Riddles.

25:35.969 --> 25:38.232
He's not the same man I knew.

25:38.319 --> 25:41.061
Well, that's a fortunate
outcome, at least.

25:41.148 --> 25:42.802
Not for my sister.

25:44.194 --> 25:45.282
It's natural that
a place like this

25:45.369 --> 25:47.328
should transform a man.

25:47.415 --> 25:49.635
I find myself anew

25:49.722 --> 25:51.941
in the silver of the mirror
every morning.

25:52.028 --> 25:54.074
Now, I take it

25:54.161 --> 25:56.424
you spoke to Captain Wale
in Quebec City?

26:00.123 --> 26:02.038
This is Mr. Charles Duquet.

26:02.125 --> 26:04.693
You may speak freely
in front of him.

26:10.960 --> 26:14.137
It is still good to meet you.

26:16.009 --> 26:17.576
I did not come here for tea.

26:17.663 --> 26:21.449
And I prefer molasses,
not honey.

26:21.536 --> 26:24.321
Captain Wale did confirm
your ties to the Company.

26:24.408 --> 26:28.151
Well, you see, I am a man
who speaks plainly.

26:29.631 --> 26:31.154
We found Lafarge's boy.

26:35.550 --> 26:38.031
Now, that is a relief.

26:38.118 --> 26:40.599
Well, it would be...

26:40.686 --> 26:42.688
if he were still alive.

26:42.775 --> 26:45.734
We found him dead,

26:45.821 --> 26:47.475
by the river.

26:47.562 --> 26:50.217
A shame.

26:50.304 --> 26:52.654
His mother will be
brought to her knees.

26:54.395 --> 26:56.527
HAMISH:
The boy's death
is on your ledger.

26:56.615 --> 26:58.138
COOKE:
No, Mr. Goames.

26:58.225 --> 26:59.879
You're mistaken.

26:59.966 --> 27:01.445
I have orders from Captain Wale

27:01.532 --> 27:03.447
to form a partnership with you.

27:03.534 --> 27:07.321
And though I find it
disagreeable,

27:07.408 --> 27:10.280
I am a Company man,

27:10.367 --> 27:12.456
and an order is an order,
after all.

27:12.543 --> 27:15.068
But I am
but a simple barrel maker.

27:17.461 --> 27:19.812
My position within these walls
hinges on the good graces

27:19.899 --> 27:21.248
of Intendant De Fer.

27:21.335 --> 27:22.771
You see, my time in the fiddle

27:22.858 --> 27:24.338
afforded me some
much needed reflection.

27:24.425 --> 27:26.993
I'm keeping my beard
low to the ground, and as such,

27:27.080 --> 27:28.516
I would point you
in the direction

27:28.603 --> 27:31.171
of a Mr. Bill Selby.

27:31.258 --> 27:32.999
He's out there
forming alliances.

27:33.086 --> 27:37.003
Perhaps your Mr. Cross
knows of his whereabouts.

27:40.093 --> 27:41.921
Good day.

27:42.008 --> 27:43.966
[chuckles]

27:59.982 --> 28:01.854
-I handled the boy.
-COOKE: And left the body

28:01.941 --> 28:04.552
for any passing fool to find?

28:04.639 --> 28:06.902
Better it look like an accident.

28:06.989 --> 28:09.513
It wasn't an accident, Charles.

28:09.600 --> 28:11.515
I see it in your eyes.

28:11.602 --> 28:13.256
It was sloppy work.

28:13.343 --> 28:15.432
I should dissolve
our partnership.

28:18.522 --> 28:21.612
That would be
an unfortunate decision.

28:21.700 --> 28:23.702
It's my decision to make.

28:26.661 --> 28:29.185
Before you make it,

28:29.272 --> 28:31.622
I would like to know
why you neglected

28:31.710 --> 28:34.625
to tell the Hudson's Bay man
about the pistols?

28:39.108 --> 28:41.458
What pistols
are you referring to?

28:53.122 --> 28:54.820
If I were going to betray you

28:54.907 --> 28:56.517
I already would have.

29:02.392 --> 29:04.394
When I found that letter
on your desk

29:04.481 --> 29:07.093
I gleaned a lot about your
arrangement to supply guns

29:07.180 --> 29:10.009
to the Hudson's Bay Company.

29:12.446 --> 29:13.882
But I must confess

29:13.969 --> 29:16.624
I am still curious
on a couple of points.

29:19.409 --> 29:22.021
It seems I have misjudged you.

29:22.108 --> 29:24.066
Where are the pistols?

29:24.153 --> 29:26.721
-I don't know.
-They were to arm the Iroquois

29:26.808 --> 29:28.941
so that they could
use them against the French.

29:31.334 --> 29:34.947
I know not
what they were intended for.

29:35.034 --> 29:38.080
I traded for them,
took my profit.

29:39.560 --> 29:41.170
That's the end of the story.

29:43.346 --> 29:44.783
[chuckles]

29:46.610 --> 29:48.612
Good, good.

30:01.190 --> 30:04.411
He saved my life.

30:04.498 --> 30:06.543
He disobeyed the clan mother.

30:06.630 --> 30:08.110
I will explain to her.

30:10.634 --> 30:13.812
You will do nothing, Trepagny.

30:13.899 --> 30:16.423
The Iroquois will now blame us.

30:18.512 --> 30:20.557
You have your man.

30:20.644 --> 30:23.778
And now I have my dead friend.

30:23.865 --> 30:26.694
It's the trade of the matter.

30:39.098 --> 30:41.927
We'll come and collect the
bodies when we have more men.

30:42.014 --> 30:43.232
Now, come.

31:02.338 --> 31:04.297
[indistinct chatter]

31:30.845 --> 31:32.891
I'd like a room.

31:32.978 --> 31:34.675
Now, what would
Monsieur Trepagny's bride

31:34.762 --> 31:36.068
be needing with a room?

31:36.155 --> 31:38.461
[scoffs]
My name is Melissande,

31:38.548 --> 31:40.028
not "Monsieur Trepagny's bride."

31:40.115 --> 31:43.336
-I haven't taken his name yet.
-Ah.

31:43.423 --> 31:47.079
And Monsieur Trepagny went off
with Captain Bouchard.

31:47.166 --> 31:50.560
They haven't returned,
and now I fear the worst.

31:50.647 --> 31:52.562
I'd like a room now.

31:52.649 --> 31:55.652
Monsieur Trepagny is in the
company of Captain Bouchard,

31:55.739 --> 31:59.569
who, if he is anything,
is stouthearted.

31:59.656 --> 32:01.789
-They will return safely.
-And if they don't?

32:06.098 --> 32:07.882
I have no rooms.

32:09.362 --> 32:10.363
Delphine?

32:14.149 --> 32:16.630
Ah.
We are full up,

32:16.717 --> 32:18.675
but she can stay with you,
if you like.

32:21.417 --> 32:22.549
DELPHINE:
It's disgusting.

32:24.855 --> 32:27.380
And it will ruin all men
who look on me with desire,

32:27.467 --> 32:30.949
-and that is the truth.
-It can't be that bad, Delphine.

32:31.036 --> 32:34.822
It's a woodcutter's mark

32:34.909 --> 32:38.130
carved just above my womb.

32:40.306 --> 32:42.047
It's red and horrible.

32:44.092 --> 32:45.964
I'm so sorry.

32:53.884 --> 32:57.671
I want to tell you
my darkest secret.

33:02.458 --> 33:03.982
I had a child

33:04.069 --> 33:06.114
before I came here.

33:06.201 --> 33:08.508
Stillborn.

33:08.595 --> 33:11.032
My father took it

33:11.119 --> 33:13.339
and buried it in the ash pile

33:13.426 --> 33:16.081
and told me not to speak of it,

33:16.168 --> 33:17.865
but everybody knew.

33:20.215 --> 33:22.739
So there.

33:22.826 --> 33:24.698
All the secrets are out,

33:24.785 --> 33:28.136
and we can live
our lives free of them.

33:28.223 --> 33:31.444
Now we're even.

33:34.316 --> 33:36.362
The man who did this to me...

33:36.449 --> 33:38.494
Say nothing of him, Delphine.

33:38.581 --> 33:41.541
Banish him from your thoughts.
Promise me.

33:45.110 --> 33:48.243
I have not told you
the whole of it.

33:48.330 --> 33:51.290
What I did, after.

33:56.730 --> 34:00.386
I beat his head in
with an axe handle

34:00.473 --> 34:03.519
while he slept
and watched him bleed out.

34:03.606 --> 34:06.522
[chuckles]

34:15.792 --> 34:18.447
He didn't deserve to live.

34:18.534 --> 34:20.319
Hm?

34:22.060 --> 34:25.150
I had to leave
my village after that.

34:25.237 --> 34:27.021
I came here.

34:29.023 --> 34:32.070
And it seems he's still with me.

34:35.638 --> 34:36.726
[door opens]

34:36.813 --> 34:39.512
Delphine.
Come.

34:39.599 --> 34:42.602
I need help preparing supper
for the Intendant.

34:46.432 --> 34:48.390
[door closes]

35:04.798 --> 35:07.888
[sighs]
Randall, we've had enough games.

35:07.975 --> 35:10.064
It's time for you
to go back to my sister.

35:11.979 --> 35:13.763
I'll show you that I'm dead.

35:15.113 --> 35:16.723
So that you may tell her

35:16.810 --> 35:18.986
the truth of that.

35:24.818 --> 35:26.863
Randall, come out of there.

35:28.952 --> 35:30.171
[sighs]

35:49.756 --> 35:52.193
Come out of there, Randall.

35:54.239 --> 35:56.197
[grunting]

35:57.590 --> 35:58.721
Randall!

36:01.811 --> 36:05.293
Leave the dirt!
It is what will make you heal.

36:07.208 --> 36:09.950
Thank you for saving me.

36:10.037 --> 36:11.604
It is no matter.

36:13.171 --> 36:14.781
Thought I was already dead.

36:14.868 --> 36:16.826
But you are alive.

36:20.743 --> 36:23.137
The priests.

36:26.184 --> 36:28.186
I couldn't save them.

36:30.449 --> 36:32.102
Prayers, words.

36:32.190 --> 36:35.149
Nothing mattered.

36:35.236 --> 36:38.457
Because they came to New France
looking for death.

36:38.544 --> 36:39.936
The Iroquois obliged,

36:40.023 --> 36:41.677
and now their blood
is in the dirt.

36:41.764 --> 36:44.593
It is a godly and ordained
conclusion,

36:44.680 --> 36:46.465
I suppose.

36:50.077 --> 36:52.384
Tell me...

36:54.168 --> 36:57.258
...when you thought it was
the end, what did you see?

36:58.346 --> 37:01.044
I saw my brother.

37:02.655 --> 37:04.134
He called to me.

37:04.222 --> 37:07.573
But you did not go to him.

37:07.660 --> 37:08.791
No.

37:10.837 --> 37:13.535
But I wanted to.

37:13.622 --> 37:15.755
BOUCHARD:
Do you know what I saw?

37:15.842 --> 37:17.844
I did not ask.

37:17.931 --> 37:20.499
The widow Mathilde Geffard.

37:20.586 --> 37:22.501
And she was holding
a bottle of brandy

37:22.588 --> 37:25.025
and a bowl of warm stew.

37:25.112 --> 37:27.767
And she had a smile for me.

37:27.854 --> 37:30.726
And I could smell the brandy

37:30.813 --> 37:33.642
and the meat gravy,
rising up through my beard.

37:33.729 --> 37:36.254
Vaporous.

37:36.341 --> 37:38.386
But then I woke.

37:38.473 --> 37:40.649
My mouth was full of blood.

37:40.736 --> 37:42.912
But I was alive.

37:42.999 --> 37:45.437
And I wish to stay that way.

37:45.524 --> 37:47.482
So let's rise,
stop all this bathing

37:47.569 --> 37:49.310
and jabber of the afterlife,

37:49.397 --> 37:52.661
and make speed for Wobik.

38:02.889 --> 38:05.457
[grunts, panting]

38:05.544 --> 38:07.023
Who is this?

38:08.590 --> 38:10.505
It is me.

38:10.592 --> 38:12.290
You're the only one

38:12.377 --> 38:14.727
the Company will believe.

38:14.814 --> 38:16.859
Show everyone I'm dead.

38:18.687 --> 38:20.733
HAMISH:
You've lost your mind, Randall.

38:20.820 --> 38:23.039
What have you done?

38:23.126 --> 38:26.913
[gasps, coughing]

38:34.137 --> 38:37.271
A settler from the creek.

38:37.358 --> 38:40.187
I killed him
in front of his son.

38:40.274 --> 38:41.971
And then...

38:43.451 --> 38:45.714
...the girl came.

38:48.238 --> 38:50.153
She smiled.

38:50.240 --> 38:52.068
You must pray for forgiveness.

38:52.155 --> 38:54.201
The Company ordered it.

38:54.288 --> 38:56.769
HAMISH:
The Company had its reasons
for clearing the creek.

38:56.856 --> 38:58.684
But it was your plan
to kill them all.

38:58.771 --> 39:01.382
And that is on your
eternal soul.

39:01.469 --> 39:03.776
You will take this thing
back to the Company,

39:03.863 --> 39:07.519
back to Alice,
and they will give me a funeral.

39:07.606 --> 39:09.782
Carry me by torchlight

39:09.869 --> 39:12.437
-to St. Paul's...
-YVON: Enough.

39:19.966 --> 39:21.141
Yvon.

39:25.319 --> 39:28.278
-Yvon!
-[grunts]

39:28.366 --> 39:30.368
[gasping]

39:43.903 --> 39:46.514
[moans]

39:49.038 --> 39:52.564
You will go back to Alice.

39:52.651 --> 39:54.392
And you will be happy.

39:58.047 --> 39:59.788
You're right, Hamish.

40:03.444 --> 40:05.707
I will...

40:06.795 --> 40:08.754
I will go back to Alice.

40:08.841 --> 40:11.234
Captain Wale said
you were to deliver something.

40:11.321 --> 40:12.410
What was it?

40:12.497 --> 40:14.281
Pistols.

40:15.413 --> 40:16.762
A barrelful.

40:18.198 --> 40:19.634
Where?

40:19.721 --> 40:22.507
I'll show you.
But first...

40:24.117 --> 40:25.727
...I must give this man

40:25.814 --> 40:27.686
a proper burial.

40:29.470 --> 40:31.385
I tire of building graves
in the woods.

40:31.472 --> 40:33.735
It is mine to build.

40:33.822 --> 40:35.389
Then we have a deal.

40:35.476 --> 40:37.086
A grave,

40:37.173 --> 40:39.306
you show us the pistols,

40:39.393 --> 40:40.916
and then you go back to Alice.

40:53.102 --> 40:55.104
♪ ♪

41:02.285 --> 41:04.244
-[indistinct chatter]
-Cooke.

41:05.898 --> 41:07.377
[harrumphs]

41:14.036 --> 41:15.995
[indistinct chatter]

41:38.365 --> 41:40.323
[indistinct chatter continues]

41:50.986 --> 41:53.685
What will you do
if Trepagny does not return?

41:53.772 --> 41:55.513
Run the estate,

41:55.600 --> 41:57.906
though there is not much there
but trees.

41:57.993 --> 42:00.343
But I see what it might become.

42:00.430 --> 42:03.129
Mathilde says he gave up Wobik
for that land.

42:03.216 --> 42:04.913
He would not
had I been with him.

42:05.000 --> 42:07.176
There's a river.
Docks, at least.

42:08.221 --> 42:10.745
He will return.

42:10.832 --> 42:12.399
You do want that, don't you?

42:12.486 --> 42:14.444
[scoffs]
I don't know what I want.

42:18.884 --> 42:20.799
You can help him
improve the Doma.

42:20.886 --> 42:22.844
Perhaps there is not
a big enough rudder

42:22.931 --> 42:25.238
in the world
to steer a man such as that.

42:25.325 --> 42:27.022
But I will try.

42:27.109 --> 42:29.503
I do believe
there is a kindness in him.

42:29.590 --> 42:32.506
I saw it on our wedding night
and once in the woods, but...

42:32.593 --> 42:36.379
but he says
that wasps follow him

42:36.466 --> 42:38.425
and die from loyalty

42:38.512 --> 42:40.383
and that the snakes
then eat the dead wasps,

42:40.470 --> 42:42.385
and because of him,

42:42.472 --> 42:43.996
there is harmony.

42:44.083 --> 42:47.608
And he prays to a rotten log

42:47.695 --> 42:49.044
and a bowl full of hair.

42:49.131 --> 42:50.785
-He sounds mad.
-Mm.

42:50.872 --> 42:52.744
He's a Cathar.

42:52.831 --> 42:54.049
He will corrupt you.

42:54.136 --> 42:56.312
[scoffs]
No.

42:57.357 --> 42:59.881
I will train him,

42:59.968 --> 43:02.231
and the Doma

43:02.318 --> 43:04.712
and all the land will be mine.

43:04.799 --> 43:08.542
More land than my father
could ever imagine.

43:08.629 --> 43:10.631
Delphine.

43:10.718 --> 43:13.765
Mr. Cooke's cup
needs refilling. Come.

43:19.509 --> 43:20.989
Shoulders back.

43:21.076 --> 43:23.078
Smile.

43:39.747 --> 43:41.836
Would you like some more?

43:56.634 --> 43:59.506
♪ ♪

44:28.361 --> 44:29.884
I'm leaving.

44:29.971 --> 44:31.277
No.

44:31.364 --> 44:32.931
Stay.

44:33.018 --> 44:35.542
Finish your food.
I've lost my appetite.

44:40.460 --> 44:42.418
-[door opens]
-[bell jingles]

44:43.942 --> 44:45.421
-[door closes]
-[bell jingles]

44:47.467 --> 44:49.077
Tonight, I could...

44:49.164 --> 44:52.037
I could almost hear you
as though you were...

44:52.124 --> 44:54.039
speaking into my ear.

44:54.126 --> 44:57.042
I remain beside you.

44:57.129 --> 44:59.479
I remain with you.

44:59.566 --> 45:01.873
I... I know
you can hear my voice.

45:01.960 --> 45:04.223
I know you can see
through my eyes.

45:04.310 --> 45:06.312
I know...

45:06.399 --> 45:08.880
GAY BILL:
Ask her where
my goddamn pistols are.

45:12.100 --> 45:14.450
Bill?

45:14.537 --> 45:17.453
[sighs]

45:17.540 --> 45:20.065
Well...

45:20.152 --> 45:23.677
It seems
the barrel king of Wobik's word

45:23.764 --> 45:26.027
ain't worth a dog's breath.

45:26.114 --> 45:28.421
Now...

45:28.508 --> 45:32.120
Elisha, I should like to have

45:32.207 --> 45:34.601
those barrels of pistols
you promised.

45:36.603 --> 45:38.257
They are lost to me.

45:38.344 --> 45:40.259
Is that so?

45:40.346 --> 45:42.217
It is.

45:43.262 --> 45:45.177
How about...

45:45.264 --> 45:48.702
I dig up what's left
of your wife...

45:48.789 --> 45:52.140
toss it in the Saint Lawrence?

45:52.227 --> 45:54.664
Randall Cross had them.

45:54.752 --> 45:57.189
And where might
he have gone off to?

45:57.276 --> 45:59.147
With another Hudson Bay man,
presumably looking

45:59.234 --> 46:00.583
for the pistols.

46:00.670 --> 46:02.716
I told them they might find you.

46:02.803 --> 46:06.198
That's very kind of you, Cooke.
Suppose they don't?

46:08.243 --> 46:10.158
Bill, that is...

46:10.245 --> 46:12.465
hardly my affair to manage.

46:13.553 --> 46:16.469
Yes.
Of course.

46:16.556 --> 46:18.863
But what you will manage

46:18.950 --> 46:20.865
is another barrel of pistols.

46:20.952 --> 46:22.867
I have no more.

46:22.954 --> 46:24.607
Elisha,

46:24.694 --> 46:26.740
the number of Iroquois
have swelled.

46:26.827 --> 46:29.177
So must the pistols.

46:29.264 --> 46:31.179
And, uh, what is your plan?

46:31.266 --> 46:32.746
[chuckles softly]

46:32.833 --> 46:35.749
The plan is less French,

46:35.836 --> 46:37.316
more land and coin.

46:37.403 --> 46:39.492
Come, now.

46:39.579 --> 46:42.451
Surely I don't have to
lay the pieces out for you.

46:42.538 --> 46:44.497
And the Iroquois?

46:44.584 --> 46:46.847
They are the right tool

46:46.934 --> 46:48.327
for the task.

46:48.414 --> 46:49.850
And you--

46:49.937 --> 46:52.766
you keep to yours.

46:52.853 --> 46:54.812
Pistols.

46:56.683 --> 46:57.989
You bastard.

47:01.906 --> 47:03.864
[whistling a tune]

47:14.135 --> 47:16.094
♪ ♪

47:23.884 --> 47:25.843
Captain on the gate!

47:40.422 --> 47:43.077
Well, come, now. We mustn't
leave the gate open long,

47:43.164 --> 47:46.080
lest some savage elements
slip in behind us.

47:52.739 --> 47:54.741
♪ ♪

48:16.676 --> 48:18.634
Brandy!

48:18.721 --> 48:20.680
[exclaims, clamoring]

